    "ai_project_name": "project_name_829546_shared",
    "display_name": "Fan Coil Monitoring",
    "description": "Classification of fan coil vibrations from off, low speed to high speed using the MLC.\n\nThis example allows you to monitor and classify the behavior of a fan, particularly those found in fan-coil HVAC units, but you can also try it on other types of rotating ventilation. Classification is based on motor vibration (high or low), and it also includes an 'immobile' class in case the fan isn't moving at all. By cloning it to your workspace, you can retrain the in-sensor AI to work with other machinery, such as motors or pumps. To use this example, make sure the board is firmly affixed to the front side of the fan\u2014that is, the side pushing the air out. For accurate classification, the board's buttons should face outward (away from the fan), and the USB port side should face downward.",
    "type": "industrial",
